Group:Đặng Hữu Nhật Quang and Hoàng Nhật Tân

SEMAT (Software Engineering Method and Theory) is an initiative to reshape software engineering such that software engineering qualifies as a rigorous discipline.

First of all, we go through the endeavador process. It starts with the way off working which applied by the team, then guides the work and thus the plan and performance of the work. The work will then create, update and changes with in the purpose of the requirements and hence develop the software system. The team is supported by the stakeholder to be able to enhance the software system to fulfill the requirement of the stakeholder.

Secondly, the solution is for the requirement to fulfill both the software system and the demand of the stakeholder, thus focused by the opportunities. After that, it will scopes and constrains the work to keep it in form. The software system requires the stakeholder to use and consume which is produced by the team. It helps the team to address the opportunity and fulfills the requirement also.

Finally, the stakeholder, which is the costumer finds the opportunity, then supports and creates the requirement for the team to update and develop the software system.
